post_text:
To the 2020 senior class:
We have never been more proud.
It's not because you earned a championship medal, or excelled in your classes, or made a knockout play performance. It's not because you led the team or dazzled in your prom outfits or marched in the band or walked across the graduation stage.

We're proud because you stayed in, despite feeling a sense of loss. You weathered the storm for your community, for humanity and for those you love. You pushed through and adapted to a new way of learning. You stayed connected, you demonstrated love to your family and friends. You learned lessons and taught lessons by doing the right thing.

You didn't know that when you walked out through the school doors in the middle of March that you were stepping into a world that was rapidly changing and unpredictable....and that you wouldn't be coming back. But you also have a bond with each other unlike any other. And you drew together by staying apart. Stay strong. You make your community proud. #EaglePride #FowlerClassof2020

It's the end of the year and a season where people extend their generosity to many worthy causes. In Fowler, we are fortunate to have a thriving school and blessed to have community support. The Fowler Public Schools Education Foundation is working to build a trust fund to provide long term financial support so our community can continue to enjoy the benefits of a vibrant school system. You may have received a letter in the mail, and for your convenience, below is a link to a GoFundMe site where you can use your credit card to donate any amount. The money raised will go towards building a trust fund and some shorter term needs within the school system. Thanks for your ongoing support and generosity and have a wonderful holiday season.

https://www.gofundme.com/FowlerSchoolsFoundation

We are proud to announce one of the first grants that we recently awarded to Ms. Rotary, K-4 Reading Interventionist, for two sets of materials to use in our intermediate grade levels.These materials are nonfiction passages that promote the ability of students to apply critical thinking skills as they engage high-interest topics. All of our students in grades 2 through 4 will have the opportunity to benefit, now and in years to come. These materials were awarded Ms. Rotary for her winning grant request, which was one of the first round of grants we awarded last year.

Thanks to the generosity of previous donors, these grants have been possible to meet shorter term needs of our schools!

Make donation to help students now and in the future: www.gofundme.com/pyk0io.

Are you shopping on Amazon for Christmas gifts?--your Amazon purchases can provide a donation to Fowler Public Schools! Just go to smile.amazon.com, then select us as your charitable organization to receive Amazon donations from eligible purchases before you begin shopping. Amazon will remember your selection each time you shop, and then every eligible purchase you make at smile.amazon.com will result in a donation. The name of your organization should appear below the search bar each time you shop.

A recent MLive article focused on which high schools in Michigan have the highest percentage of graduates who have completed a degree or certificate within 6 years of leaving high school. The most recent 6 year data is reflected for the Class of 2008 for which FHS ranked 4th in the state with 73% of our graduates having earned a college diploma or certificate within 6 years. There are over 1300 public high schools in Michigan. What a credit to our kids, staff, parents, and community!!

http://www.mlive.com/news/index.ssf/2016/02/which_michigan_counties_are_pr.html#37

post_text:
There have been some questions as to how donations will be used.

A committee comprised of community members that are on the Foundation Board will decide on the disbursement of funds. This committee will work closely with the administration and school board to prioritize and choose the most appropriate areas of need.

The goal is that donations will create an endowment fund similar to what one might see at a university. It will exist in perpetuity, with continual growth, and provide interest which will eventually be used to support the school each year.

In the short term, some of the funds may be provided directly to Fowler Public Schools for priority needs. The Foundation will set donation goals and when those are reached, funds will be disbursed. The funds may potentially be used for classroom and technology improvements, specific projects or programs or other areas that support classroom instruction.
